        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="756" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d756">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/10–2245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moreland</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-22">October 22,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received October 22—10:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>401. Immediately following wide local publicity given correspondence between
                    President Roosevelt and King Ibn Saud, all Baghdad newspapers this morning
                    front-paged text of Regent’s letter of March 10 to President Roosevelt and late
                    President’s reply dated April 12.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moreland</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
